Description: vakargo is a P2P marketplace that leverages unused personal luggage space and commercial cargo space to make shipping more efficient.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: The globalized world we live in allows us to exchange information instantaneously, but we often forget how difficult it is to send a simple package. Sending goods internationally can be extremely costly from a time and money perspective because of inefficiencies with logistics companies. vakargo aims to leverage the existing human network of world travelers to get items delivered in a timely manner and for a reasonable price. The idea originated from the founders’ personal experiences when trying to ship items from the United States to friends and family in Vietnam. Frequently, packages are transferred from company to company until it reaches its destination, resulting in items being late, damaged, or missing. Christmas packages delivered to missionaries in India were not received until February, and were ultimately found to be empty boxes. Electronics sent to family in Vietnam were never  received. A drafting pen from Tokyo took 8 weeks to arrive in Oklahoma. Asside from process inefficiencies, there are also cost inefficiencies. Shipping small items to Vietnam can be up to $200, while delivering a television only 250 miles from Dallas, TX to Norman, OK can be more than $100. Because of these issues, people have resorted to utilizing their social network and “hiring” friends who travel to deliver items, but the opportunities are infrequent on a small scale. vakargo can create connections between people who need items shipped with people who travel in order to make the delivery process efficient, reliable, and of fair value. Peer-to-peer businesses have proven to be successful across many industries, and vakargo looks to leverage the concept of social sharing in order to provide a much-needed alternative for people around the world. Though vakargo does not create “extra space” in a suitcase, it provides the network to access it. Travelers can provide their itinerary details and amount of extra space they have in their luggage. Users needing to ship items can search through listings based on the shipping destination and time frame to select a traveler and negotiate terms. Using the existing infrastructure from airlines, vakargo users can send items internationally overnight and at a fair price! And most importantly, both users can benefit from little effort. vakargo has conducted an initial pilot studies and launch events to test its hypothesis and growing user base.

Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: Yellow Bridge Interactive is a full-service web design firm that provides design and development solutions for companies of all sizes. We are a tight-knit web design and development company headquartered in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. But don't let our small town roots fool you. We are experienced in dealing with projects and clients of all sizes. In the years that we have been in business, we have set up countless websites for companies from all quarters of the United States. Every client comes to us with fresh ideas and new challenges, inspiring us to always achieve higher standards in our work to produce the best designs possible. With every project, our aim is to create sleek and functional designs that allow our clients' visions for their websites to come to life. To accomplish this, our team specializes in optimizing open source solutions to custom fit each of our clients' needs. This means that we can deliver at a faster turn-around time and at a considerably smaller cost. All of our sites are built upon content management platforms with full training available. We educate and follow up with our clients to ensure that they can use their new business tool to its fullest potential. With any project we follow the following steps to make sure your website is making the most impact for your business: ANALYZE  The crucial first step in any web project is to clearly know both your goals and your industry. We analyze your current website as well as take a look at what your neighbors have been up to. DESIGN After a plan is in place, we task our skilled designers with crafting an innovative website design that fully captures the client's vision and puts it on the screen. DEVELOP Our talented web developers custom create SEO friendly HTML code that meets and even exceeds today's standards, following best practices and accounting for changes in the online community. TEST Any successful site requires a good deal of testing. We make sure that the site performs smoothly on all modern browsers and devices prior to making a public launch. LAUNCH When the site is launched, we take care to preserve any traffic value that has already been built up. Utilizing special redirects and coding techniques ensures that your new site has a strong start. STAY IN TOUCH Once we hand you the keys to your brand new website, our team will keep in touch to make sure that you keep moving ahead flawlessly and are getting the most out of our product.
